1
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:06,596
[North of Thailand]

2
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,480
In a faraway valley in
the north of Thailand

3
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:14,040
there is a village situated
amidst undefiled nature,

4
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:16,280
cut off from the outside world.

5
00:00:16,977 --> 00:00:20,720
A special tribe called
'Mudan' lives in this place.

6
00:01:29,137 --> 00:01:30,138
Gaysorn

7
00:01:31,070 --> 00:01:35,400
you are an heir of Mudan tribe.

8
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:39,280
You are now 20 years old

9
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:43,120
and your body will be fragrant.

10
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:49,560
It's even more fragrant
than all the flowers.

11
00:01:49,999 --> 00:01:51,359
In this world,

12
00:02:17,483 --> 00:02:19,240
beautiful flowers come with danger.

13
00:02:19,630 --> 00:02:23,680
Greedy people will try
to benefit from your scent.

14
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,080
You have to be careful.

15
00:02:26,713 --> 00:02:29,840
Don't trust the outsiders, ever.

16
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,500
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 1)

17
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,237
Good afternoon to our
honored guests and the press.

18
00:03:55,347 --> 00:03:58,477
Please welcome Mr. Wittaya Sukontawanich,

19
00:03:58,507 --> 00:04:01,187
chairman of Sukontawanich Company,

20
00:04:01,327 --> 00:04:04,628
and the executive of scented
products named 'Kusuma'.

21
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:11,597
It is well-known that our brand, Kusuma,

22
00:04:11,837 --> 00:04:13,357
a high-end perfume brand

23
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,037
is expanding to the global market.

24
00:04:15,757 --> 00:04:17,317
Our selling point is that

25
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:20,477
the scent has been extracted
from true natural products.

26
00:04:20,997 --> 00:04:22,517
Despite the fact that these past years

27
00:04:22,914 --> 00:04:25,277
our company faced with
some difficulties such as

28
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,278
a revenue shortfall,

29
00:04:27,627 --> 00:04:29,517
I still believe that this year

30
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:31,517
Kusuma will come back and be great again

31
00:04:31,917 --> 00:04:35,317
under the supervision of our
new generation of executives.

32
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,397
I'd like to introduce

33
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,477
Mr. Phummarak Sukontawanich,

34
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:42,037
Kusuma's new Vice President.

35
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:50,248
Hello, everyone.

36
00:04:51,534 --> 00:04:53,317
As you all know,

37
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,597
Mr. Anurak Sukontawanich,

38
00:04:56,380 --> 00:04:59,477
our former chairman is my father.

39
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:03,357
He focused on research
and developed new scent.

40
00:05:05,389 --> 00:05:06,957
After facing some health problems,

41
00:05:07,693 --> 00:05:11,030
our Kusuma brand was in haitus.

42
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:15,957
As his son, I will step
in and continue his work.

43
00:05:17,388 --> 00:05:19,437
Kusuma will launch new products.

44
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,117
We will introduce our new scent

45
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,997
which will be the one
and only scent in the world.

46
00:05:26,727 --> 00:05:28,537
We are now developing this new scent

47
00:05:29,594 --> 00:05:31,954
and grand press conference will be hosted
when we are ready.

48
00:05:32,754 --> 00:05:34,154
Please stay tuned for the new scent

49
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,081
and I will see you later.

50
00:05:37,877 --> 00:05:40,437
Good thing we didn't
host the event outdoors,

51
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,213
we just lied up there and
could've been struck by lightning.

52
00:05:42,237 --> 00:05:43,717
Oh, come on.

53
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:45,757
We need to make it go viral.

54
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,037
I did what you asked me
to already, what's next?

55
00:05:49,677 --> 00:05:53,037
What do you mean by a new scent
that will change our company completely?

56
00:05:55,507 --> 00:05:56,707
Can you just calm down, Scent?

57
00:05:57,387 --> 00:05:59,397
This is your first day since you got back.

58
00:05:59,854 --> 00:06:01,917
I think you should go home and rest.

59
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,240
You can take care of your father as well.

60
00:06:29,684 --> 00:06:30,727
Thank you so much

61
00:06:31,747 --> 00:06:33,597
for taking care of him when I'm not around.

62
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:37,277
Your father is my elder brother.

63
00:06:37,757 --> 00:06:38,787
How can I leave him?

64
00:06:47,247 --> 00:06:48,248
Dad,

65
00:06:49,517 --> 00:06:50,557
I'm back.

66
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:52,997
I just graduated.

67
00:06:54,717 --> 00:06:57,437
This time, I will be with you

68
00:06:59,747 --> 00:07:00,748
and I will not leave you.

69
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:11,437
Do you know why your dad became like this?

70
00:07:15,757 --> 00:07:18,717
The doctor said that his stroke was caused
from stress, wasn't it?

71
00:07:19,647 --> 00:07:20,648
Well,

72
00:07:21,677 --> 00:07:23,557
it is not just stress from work.

73
00:07:24,334 --> 00:07:25,335
There is a real reason.

74
00:07:26,574 --> 00:07:27,575
What do you mean?

75
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:32,197
20 years ago, we lauched
a perfume called 'Bussaba',

76
00:07:33,334 --> 00:07:35,335
and it brought a good
reputation to the company.

77
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,437
It was the reason behind our wealth.

78
00:07:40,214 --> 00:07:41,215
I see.

79
00:07:41,874 --> 00:07:45,157
I was so young back then, but we
suddenly stopped producing the product.

80
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:49,714
That was because we couldn't create
that scent any longer.

81
00:07:50,437 --> 00:07:51,438
Why was that?

82
00:07:54,434 --> 00:07:56,557
We ran out of the source to produce it.

83
00:07:57,907 --> 00:08:00,399
Your dad tried to find alternative sources.

84
00:08:01,174 --> 00:08:04,437
He had been searching for years
but he couldn't. It reached to the point

85
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:07,317
that his stress caused a
stroke five years ago.

86
00:08:09,054 --> 00:08:10,997
Where did that scent come from?

87
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,121
This is the Mudan tribe.

88
00:08:16,974 --> 00:08:20,637
People from this tribe can
produce fragrance from their bodies.

89
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:24,207
People with a fragrant smell?

90
00:08:27,774 --> 00:08:30,837
Like musk deer and small Indian civet?

91
00:08:33,359 --> 00:08:35,397
We used to have one person from Mudan.

92
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:39,397
And we extracted his body scent
to produce Bussaba perfume.

93
00:08:45,787 --> 00:08:46,797
Believe it or not,

94
00:08:48,854 --> 00:08:51,157
you could make your dad's dream come true.

95
00:08:53,317 --> 00:08:54,318
It's possible that

96
00:08:55,808 --> 00:08:57,877
this could heal your dad.

97
00:09:07,957 --> 00:09:09,597
Where do the Mudan people live?

98
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,637
They live deep in the forest,
located on the high moutains.

99
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:19,000
They occasionally sent some of them
to sell their products in the city.

100
00:09:19,347 --> 00:09:22,037
They never introduce
where they live to anyone.

101
00:09:27,857 --> 00:09:28,858
Hello, Sun?

102
00:09:30,157 --> 00:09:31,277
I'm in Chiang Mai right now.

103
00:09:31,851 --> 00:09:33,171
What are you doing in Chiang Mai?

104
00:09:33,877 --> 00:09:37,397
Stop asking too many question,
I need you to find me a navigator.

105
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,954
Navigator? Where to?

106
00:09:42,607 --> 00:09:43,608
Mudan.

107
00:09:58,894 --> 00:09:59,895
This way.

108
00:10:02,147 --> 00:10:03,148
Easy there.

109
00:10:08,654 --> 00:10:09,655
This way, sir.

110
00:10:22,014 --> 00:10:23,015
Follow me.

111
00:11:15,407 --> 00:11:16,408
Where are you heading to?

112
00:11:16,917 --> 00:11:19,118
I'm taking him to trek through the forest.

113
00:11:20,117 --> 00:11:22,037
You can't. We just found
elephants this morning.

114
00:11:22,114 --> 00:11:24,157
Well, you shouldn't step
outside the national park.

115
00:11:24,647 --> 00:11:27,160
It's dangerous and nobody
could save you in time.

116
00:11:27,414 --> 00:11:28,877
It's okay, I can take care of him.

117
00:11:29,415 --> 00:11:30,937
Please? Please, sir?

118
00:11:31,581 --> 00:11:33,301
Fine. Go ahead.

119
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,461
Thank you.

120
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:36,077
Let's go, sir.

121
00:11:36,837 --> 00:11:38,157
We're clear, follow me.

122
00:11:47,197 --> 00:11:49,837
Gaysorn.

123
00:11:53,354 --> 00:11:54,355
Gaysorn.

124
00:11:57,247 --> 00:11:58,248
Gaysorn.

125
00:12:04,454 --> 00:12:05,677
What are you doing here?

126
00:12:06,557 --> 00:12:08,197
Just sitting and thinking about things.

127
00:12:08,757 --> 00:12:09,758
Tawan,

128
00:12:10,507 --> 00:12:13,244
what does the world down there
look like? I've never seen it.

129
00:12:13,597 --> 00:12:14,727
Too hectic.

130
00:12:15,598 --> 00:12:17,678
Too many people.
It's not as comfortable as our home.

131
00:12:18,287 --> 00:12:21,657
Can you take me there next time?

132
00:12:21,837 --> 00:12:24,197
No, you can't go. Mata won't let you

133
00:12:27,397 --> 00:12:28,398
and neither will I.

134
00:12:30,157 --> 00:12:32,557
You expect me to stay on the moutain
for the rest of my life?

135
00:12:36,197 --> 00:12:37,454
You are special.

136
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:40,477
You're an heir of our tribe leader.

137
00:12:40,827 --> 00:12:42,397
What are we gonna do if you got hurt?

138
00:12:43,757 --> 00:12:46,677
There are millions of people down there
and not one of them is a good person?

139
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,297
That's right. Let's go.

140
00:12:56,054 --> 00:12:57,557
I've never seen this tribe before.

141
00:12:57,989 --> 00:13:00,077
My dad used to tell
me a stories about them.

142
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:02,100
He said that this is the way to the tribe.

143
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:03,158
Just follow me.

144
00:13:04,214 --> 00:13:05,215
Let's go.

145
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:26,277
Do you really know where they live?

146
00:13:27,237 --> 00:13:28,877
This way, follow me.

147
00:13:34,517 --> 00:13:36,317
Follow me, sir.

148
00:13:43,147 --> 00:13:44,707
It's about to rain, we should get back.

149
00:13:45,194 --> 00:13:47,677
You go ahead, I'll visit
my mom's house first.

150
00:14:05,394 --> 00:14:06,747
This is not good.

151
00:14:07,837 --> 00:14:09,367
It's about to rain, heavy rain.

152
00:14:10,847 --> 00:14:12,007
What's the problem with that?

153
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:14,268
If it rains,

154
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,000
the path won't be good enough to trek.

155
00:14:17,707 --> 00:14:19,917
I think we should head back.

156
00:14:20,437 --> 00:14:22,538
We can't go back, I already paid you.

157
00:14:22,837 --> 00:14:25,917
Such a waste of time, you got me walking
around in circles since the morning.

158
00:14:25,954 --> 00:14:28,197
Do you really know the
way to the Mudan tribe?

159
00:14:29,154 --> 00:14:30,477
Where exactly are the Mudan people?

160
00:14:31,334 --> 00:14:33,197
I mean… people said
they live around here.

161
00:14:33,837 --> 00:14:36,838
If it is around here, then we should go.
You took my money already.

162
00:14:37,127 --> 00:14:39,637
I'm not leaving until I see them,
or I need a refund.

163
00:14:40,037 --> 00:14:41,038
Go!

164
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:48,301
- I'm leaving!
- Hey!

165
00:14:48,757 --> 00:14:50,358
Hey! Hey!

166
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:55,901
Damn it!

167
00:18:23,517 --> 00:18:24,518
Your scent…

168
00:18:28,677 --> 00:18:29,678
What are you doing?

169
00:20:41,534 --> 00:20:42,535
You smell so good.

170
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,401
You're up?

171
00:20:59,580 --> 00:21:00,581
What is that smell?

172
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:08,487
From wildflowers.

173
00:21:10,837 --> 00:21:11,838
What kind of flower?

174
00:21:12,838 --> 00:21:13,839
I'm not familiar with it.

175
00:21:15,154 --> 00:21:17,077
You know all flower's scents.

176
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:20,268
Never mind.

177
00:21:23,870 --> 00:21:25,150
So, where are we?

178
00:21:29,887 --> 00:21:30,888
Ouch!

179
00:21:33,587 --> 00:21:34,588
Ouch!

180
00:21:39,027 --> 00:21:40,028
You should lie still.

181
00:21:41,227 --> 00:21:42,380
Tell me where am I?

182
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:44,874
This is my mom's house.

183
00:21:46,997 --> 00:21:48,677
I saw you lying down unconscious.

184
00:21:50,077 --> 00:21:52,878
What happened to you? Just stay still.

185
00:22:02,797 --> 00:22:03,957
I fell off the mountain.

186
00:22:07,894 --> 00:22:08,895
Well..

187
00:22:11,007 --> 00:22:12,637
I'll get you new clothes to change into.

188
00:22:13,526 --> 00:22:14,527
Just lie down.

189
00:23:40,980 --> 00:23:41,981
Let me help.

190
00:24:27,537 --> 00:24:28,638
That nice smell again.

191
00:24:34,837 --> 00:24:35,838
What are you doing?

192
00:24:36,394 --> 00:24:37,957
I smell it from you.

193
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:39,701
You mean from this?

194
00:24:42,454 --> 00:24:43,455
No.

195
00:24:50,860 --> 00:24:51,861
Let me heal your wound.

196
00:25:16,957 --> 00:25:17,958
Where do you come from?

197
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:20,741
I'm from the city.

198
00:25:23,077 --> 00:25:26,628
I followed the huntsman to the forest.

199
00:25:28,147 --> 00:25:30,957
What were you doing in the forest?

200
00:25:33,020 --> 00:25:34,277
I'm looking for someone.

201
00:25:35,952 --> 00:25:38,469
Have you ever heard of the Mudan tribe?

202
00:25:42,797 --> 00:25:43,957
You've heard about it, right?

203
00:25:47,814 --> 00:25:48,815
Nope.

204
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:52,197
Mudan people produce
fragrance from their bodies.

205
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,160
People say that they live around here.

206
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,277
- You know them?
- There is no such thing.

207
00:25:58,220 --> 00:26:01,060
People producing fragrance
from the bodies? It's a myth.

208
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:06,381
You should rest.

209
00:26:07,847 --> 00:26:09,767
When you get better, I'll lead
you to the edge of the forest.

210
00:26:10,877 --> 00:26:11,878
So you can go home.

211
00:26:12,067 --> 00:26:13,107
You will come back, right?

212
00:26:14,727 --> 00:26:15,967
I'll find you something to eat.

213
00:26:26,127 --> 00:26:27,557
I talked to the police,

214
00:26:27,714 --> 00:26:29,954
they found the huntsman that
took Scent to the forest but

215
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:32,877
he lost Scent after the heavy rain.

216
00:26:33,514 --> 00:26:34,515
What the hell?

217
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:37,117
He left his boss in the
middle of the forest?

218
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:41,941
Don't worry.

219
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:45,317
I'll fly there tomorrow
morning to look for him.

220
00:26:45,854 --> 00:26:46,855
Good.

221
00:26:47,047 --> 00:26:48,837
You are his one and only best friend,

222
00:26:49,014 --> 00:26:50,077
please look for him.

223
00:26:59,477 --> 00:27:00,478
Are you done with this?

224
00:27:02,067 --> 00:27:04,167
Smells so good, can I get one?

225
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:08,077
- Gaysorn, where are you?
- Uncle?

226
00:27:08,194 --> 00:27:10,314
Have you seen my clothes?
I hung them here last night.

227
00:27:10,437 --> 00:27:12,397
Gaysorn, where are you?

228
00:27:13,127 --> 00:27:14,128
Gaysorn.

229
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:16,160
Who are you yelling for?

230
00:27:17,100 --> 00:27:18,277
Have you seen Gaysorn?

231
00:27:18,794 --> 00:27:20,317
I haven't.

232
00:27:20,957 --> 00:27:23,237
He could've gone to the
forest to get some food.

233
00:27:24,357 --> 00:27:25,937
To the forest or to the city.

234
00:27:28,820 --> 00:27:29,821
What did you say?

235
00:27:30,754 --> 00:27:32,755
He told me that he
wanted to go to the city.

236
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,682
He can't.

237
00:27:34,814 --> 00:27:37,317
You need to find him now, he can't go.

238
00:27:38,954 --> 00:27:39,955
Let's go!

239
00:27:40,834 --> 00:27:42,035
What is wrong with you?

240
00:28:58,840 --> 00:28:59,841
Hey.

241
00:29:07,020 --> 00:29:08,557
You're up?

242
00:29:11,414 --> 00:29:12,537
The air is so pure here.

243
00:29:13,714 --> 00:29:16,297
I can smell flowers, grass,

244
00:29:19,140 --> 00:29:20,141
even the dew.

245
00:29:23,234 --> 00:29:24,237
Your nose works so well.

246
00:29:25,397 --> 00:29:27,717
Sure, I do. I work in perf…

247
00:29:34,227 --> 00:29:35,337
My name is Scent.

248
00:29:43,877 --> 00:29:47,557
Thank you for saving my life.

249
00:29:52,700 --> 00:29:53,701
Gaysorn.

250
00:29:55,577 --> 00:29:56,678
Gaysorn? Like pollen?

251
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:00,601
It's a woman's name.

252
00:30:02,494 --> 00:30:03,677
Flowers are flowers.

253
00:30:04,847 --> 00:30:06,317
They are genderless.

254
00:30:10,314 --> 00:30:11,315
You're right.

255
00:30:12,277 --> 00:30:14,597
Flowers are flowers.

256
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:32,821
I smell it again.

257
00:30:39,514 --> 00:30:40,515
It smells so nice.

258
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,240
I've never smelled
anything like this before.

259
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:52,808
- Are you sure it's not from you?
- Let's eat.

260
00:30:54,994 --> 00:30:56,154
I prepared something for you.

261
00:31:05,677 --> 00:31:09,317
People from this tribe can
produce fragrance from their bodies.

262
00:31:09,797 --> 00:31:11,877
You need to pay attention to people
and the surroundings.

263
00:31:23,687 --> 00:31:24,688
Can you eat it?

264
00:31:27,527 --> 00:31:28,528
I think so.

265
00:31:48,247 --> 00:31:50,620
This chili paste smells
good too. From what?

266
00:31:53,474 --> 00:31:54,475
It's Ma Kuang.

267
00:31:54,954 --> 00:31:57,477
You really have good nose,
are you sure you're not a dog?

268
00:32:20,674 --> 00:32:23,557
Are you sure you don't
know the Mudan tribe?

269
00:32:26,574 --> 00:32:27,575
Gaysorn.

270
00:32:28,647 --> 00:32:29,648
Gaysorn.

271
00:32:30,667 --> 00:32:31,668
Gaysorn.

272
00:32:33,437 --> 00:32:34,438
Gaysorn.

273
00:32:35,767 --> 00:32:36,768
What?

274
00:32:37,067 --> 00:32:38,068
- What?
- Gaysorn!

275
00:32:38,334 --> 00:32:39,335
- Hey.
- Listen.

276
00:32:39,607 --> 00:32:40,797
- Gaysorn.
- Be quiet.

277
00:32:41,014 --> 00:32:43,397
- Don't say anything and don't go outside.
- What?

278
00:32:44,647 --> 00:32:45,648
Gaysorn.

279
00:32:50,634 --> 00:32:51,635
Tawan.

280
00:32:53,477 --> 00:32:54,478
Is everything okay?

281
00:32:56,814 --> 00:32:59,117
Mata asked me to look
for you, where were you?

282
00:33:01,707 --> 00:33:03,094
I… well…

283
00:33:03,447 --> 00:33:05,207
I went to get mushrooms
and some vegetables.

284
00:33:05,694 --> 00:33:06,797
Why?

285
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:10,437
She was worried that
you would go down there,

286
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,281
and so was I.

287
00:33:14,994 --> 00:33:17,437
Tawan, I'm an adult.

288
00:33:18,597 --> 00:33:21,077
I can walk and go wherever I want to.

289
00:33:23,614 --> 00:33:24,615
Gaysorn.

290
00:33:25,327 --> 00:33:26,328
Gaysorn.

291
00:33:47,447 --> 00:33:48,448
Is everything okay?

292
00:33:49,134 --> 00:33:50,135
Yeah.

293
00:33:51,474 --> 00:33:52,475
Liar.

294
00:33:53,574 --> 00:33:55,974
If it was really nothing,
why did you ask me to hide in here?

295
00:33:56,867 --> 00:33:58,317
They are not fond of strangers.

296
00:34:00,877 --> 00:34:04,157
If they found out that I brought an
outsider here, they wouldn't be pleased.

297
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,080
Are you trying to hide something?

298
00:34:12,257 --> 00:34:13,258
Planting opium poppies?

299
00:34:14,234 --> 00:34:15,235
Drug dealers?

300
00:34:21,237 --> 00:34:22,238
I was just kidding.

301
00:34:23,037 --> 00:34:25,717
But if there is really nothing,
why are you afraid of the outsiders?

302
00:34:29,194 --> 00:34:30,714
What's wrong with being the outsiders?

303
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,081
I mean...

304
00:34:47,937 --> 00:34:49,238
My mom went to the city

305
00:34:50,826 --> 00:34:52,786
and she disappeared.
She never come back here.

306
00:34:53,660 --> 00:34:56,757
Disappeared? Like completely gone?

307
00:34:57,357 --> 00:34:59,534
That's right. More than 10 years now.

308
00:35:00,157 --> 00:35:02,957
She didn't come back.
She didn't send any letters.

309
00:35:03,974 --> 00:35:05,237
Nobody knew where she was

310
00:35:06,477 --> 00:35:07,879
or how she was doing.

311
00:35:12,887 --> 00:35:14,847
Mata said that my mom
went there to rescue my dad

312
00:35:16,860 --> 00:35:17,997
but she didn't come back.

313
00:35:19,007 --> 00:35:20,537
Mata believed that

314
00:35:22,008 --> 00:35:23,737
people there could…

315
00:35:37,277 --> 00:35:38,278
My deepest condolences.

316
00:35:47,007 --> 00:35:49,037
Mata said that my mom
wouldn't come back here.

317
00:35:52,597 --> 00:35:54,298
But I hope that she is still alive

318
00:35:57,754 --> 00:35:59,397
somewhere in this world.

319
00:36:12,074 --> 00:36:14,074
Every family has to deal
with something difficult.

320
00:36:16,314 --> 00:36:17,317
My dad is still alive.

321
00:36:20,077 --> 00:36:21,078
But he is bedridden

322
00:36:22,117 --> 00:36:23,477
like a puppet who can breathe.

323
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:25,837
He can't talk.

324
00:36:28,657 --> 00:36:29,658
What are you going to do?

325
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:34,481
I will do whatever it takes
to bring him back to normal.

326
00:36:39,914 --> 00:36:41,315
And I will find my mom.

327
00:36:48,557 --> 00:36:49,758
It will come true one day,

328
00:36:50,854 --> 00:36:51,855
right?

329
00:37:15,074 --> 00:37:16,075
- Wow!
- Oh my!

330
00:37:16,837 --> 00:37:18,077
- It's huge!
- So huge!

331
00:37:24,954 --> 00:37:25,955
Get it up here.

332
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,940
Wait.

333
00:37:31,397 --> 00:37:32,957
Where is Gaysorn? He's not joining us?

334
00:37:35,254 --> 00:37:36,255
I'm here.

335
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:43,117
Malee. Renu.

336
00:37:43,287 --> 00:37:44,288
Gaysorn.

337
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,880
I wish you two stay together forever.

338
00:37:47,180 --> 00:37:48,181
Thank you so much.

339
00:37:49,044 --> 00:37:52,077
When you get married,

340
00:37:52,407 --> 00:37:54,937
Malee and I will give it back to you.

341
00:37:57,715 --> 00:37:59,917
- Come on, let me help you.
- Sure.

342
00:38:00,340 --> 00:38:02,357
Come to think of it,

343
00:38:02,877 --> 00:38:05,557
Seeing these two getting married

344
00:38:05,797 --> 00:38:08,398
makes me want to get married
as well. Isn't it right, Tawan?

345
00:38:15,047 --> 00:38:17,567
Tawan, don't forget to tell us
when you decided to get married.

346
00:38:19,437 --> 00:38:21,438
Gaysorn, are you blushing?

347
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,281
Gaysorn.

348
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:54,682
Thank you.

349
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:03,107
Are you thinking about your mom?

350
00:39:06,307 --> 00:39:07,308
Mata,

351
00:39:09,354 --> 00:39:10,355
can I ask you something?

352
00:39:13,547 --> 00:39:16,157
Some of us went down
there to search for your mom.

353
00:39:17,534 --> 00:39:19,077
But no one heard anything about her.

354
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:25,557
Your mom went to
Bangkok and the city is huge.

355
00:39:25,734 --> 00:39:27,357
How can we find her?

356
00:39:33,314 --> 00:39:36,315
I don't want to say it but I have to.

357
00:39:38,067 --> 00:39:39,917
It's been more than 10 years.

358
00:39:40,774 --> 00:39:42,557
If she was still alive,

359
00:39:44,197 --> 00:39:46,437
she would come back to
you for sure, don't you think?

360
00:39:50,717 --> 00:39:53,937
We circle back to
this conclusion every time.

361
00:39:56,427 --> 00:39:57,428
Gaysorn!

362
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:02,677
Can you help us here?

363
00:40:03,587 --> 00:40:04,608
Sure.

364
00:40:05,387 --> 00:40:06,388
I should go.

365
00:40:18,430 --> 00:40:22,230
I feel bad for him. I mean, that's his mom.

366
00:40:23,357 --> 00:40:24,517
You can't go soft.

367
00:40:26,727 --> 00:40:27,957
If you really love him,

368
00:40:29,127 --> 00:40:31,597
you can't let him go down there, ever.

369
00:40:55,214 --> 00:40:57,157
Hey! Where do you think you're going?

370
00:40:58,540 --> 00:40:59,541
Get back inside.

371
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:03,360
You want me to stay in the
cottage all day and night?

372
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:06,517
- I already told you…
- That I can't let anyone see me.

373
00:41:07,077 --> 00:41:10,037
I'm well aware of that
and this is during the night.

374
00:41:11,287 --> 00:41:14,167
Your cottage is situated so far from
the village, who would see me here?

375
00:41:15,617 --> 00:41:18,637
Well, can you take me to stargazing?

376
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:24,077
I want to see how pretty
the stars can be from up here.

377
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:27,421
Please.

378
00:41:28,047 --> 00:41:31,277
Please! Come on, Gaysorn.

379
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:49,601
What about Bangkok?

380
00:41:52,527 --> 00:41:53,528
Is it far from here?

381
00:41:56,129 --> 00:41:57,969
Why did you ask? Do
you want to go to Bangkok?

382
00:42:00,937 --> 00:42:03,677
Well… maybe.

383
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:08,660
I just want to know
how far it is from here.

384
00:42:12,900 --> 00:42:16,597
It's about the same distance
from here to Chiang Mai,

385
00:42:17,597 --> 00:42:18,598
multiplied by five.

386
00:42:23,917 --> 00:42:24,918
What?

387
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:28,040
Don't tell me that you have
never been to Chiang Mai.

388
00:42:28,597 --> 00:42:29,798
I've never been anywhere.

389
00:42:31,414 --> 00:42:32,415
Are you kidding me?

390
00:42:37,597 --> 00:42:38,837
I want to go to Bangkok.

391
00:42:40,820 --> 00:42:41,957
I want to look for my mom.

392
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:57,041
Gaysorn.

393
00:42:58,277 --> 00:42:59,278
Gaysorn.

394
00:43:01,327 --> 00:43:03,719
Renu and Malee asked you
to secure these fabric's ends.

395
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:06,121
Gaysorn.

396
00:43:07,540 --> 00:43:08,541
Gaysorn.

397
00:43:13,707 --> 00:43:14,708
He is not here.

398
00:43:15,947 --> 00:43:17,997
He went back here already. Where is he now?

399
00:43:27,807 --> 00:43:30,087
Hey! Did you hear that?

400
00:43:30,837 --> 00:43:33,317
What is that sound? Someone is coming?

401
00:43:36,600 --> 00:43:38,277
We need to hide. Come on!

402
00:43:42,637 --> 00:43:43,638
What is it?

403
00:44:09,207 --> 00:44:10,208
That smell.

404
00:44:13,847 --> 00:44:15,637
I think I smell it from…

405
00:44:29,557 --> 00:44:30,558
That sound is gone.

406
00:44:31,680 --> 00:44:32,685
We should go.

407
00:44:44,554 --> 00:44:45,655
Who are you?

408
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:01,160
(Next Episode) I'm just a tourist
who got lost in the woods.

409
00:45:01,185 --> 00:45:01,516
You're lying!

410
00:45:04,383 --> 00:45:06,302
- There’s a fire!
- Quick, get some water!

411
00:45:07,140 --> 00:45:08,979
We don't even know what happened to Mom.

412
00:45:08,980 --> 00:45:10,430
Maybe she's still alive.

413
00:45:10,431 --> 00:45:11,340
Is that why you're helping him?

414
00:45:11,341 --> 00:45:14,020
You just want to hang out with them, right?

415
00:45:15,811 --> 00:45:17,111
I just want to be your friend.

416
00:45:17,120 --> 00:45:18,751
You can't trust outsiders.

417
00:45:18,775 --> 00:45:19,775
But I trust him.

418
00:45:25,461 --> 00:45:26,609
Come to Bangkok with me.

419
00:45:26,811 --> 00:45:29,918
If you want to find your mother,
I'll help you.

